Banco Pastor Shareholders to Accept Popular Bid, ABC Says

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-10-09T09:59:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/banco-pastor-shareholders-to-accept-popular-bid-abc-says.html
Shareholders of  Banco Pastor SA (PAS)  are
set to accept a takeover bid from  Banco Popular Espanol SA (POP) 
following a board meeting yesterday,  ABC newspaper reported .  Three of the lender’s biggest shareholders, Fundacion
Barrie, Amancio Ortega’s Pontegadea Inversiones SL and
Financiere Tesalia SA, told Pastor Chairman Jose Maria Arias
they plan to accept Popular’s 1.3 billion-euro ($1.7 billion)
offer, ABC said, without saying how it obtained the information.  The three shareholders control 52.1 percent of Pastor,
enough to ensure the offer goes through, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net  